1.title: The Koalas of Kangaroo Island

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Faulkner travels to Kangaroo Island to explore how koala populations are being protected by conservationists. In addition, he and his associates encounter a blue-tongue lizard with a bizarre physical abnormality at the Reptile Park.

2.title: The Endangered Numbat

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Faulkner learns what is being done to save the endangered numbat population during a trip to the Dryandra Woodland in Western Australia. Along the way, he encounters a Mitchell's short-tailed snake and meets some baby woylies.

3.title: Billy the Kid

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Faulkner along with his son Billy make the rounds at the Reptile Park meeting kangaroos, crocodiles, pythons, dingoes and parrots.

4.title: The Critters of Western Australia

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Faulkner encounters quokkas, king skinks and Australian fur seals during his trip to Rottnest Island. On the mainland, he interacts with endangered woylies at the Western Australian Conservation Center.

5.title: The Mystique of Cape Leveque

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: Faulkner discovers new uses for seashells, finds exotic creatures, and learns a little Aboriginal history to endangered woylies during a trip to Cape Leveque in Western Australia.

6.title: Tim's Most Dangerous Jobs

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Faulkner's risky assignments include cleaning the alligator lagoon; entering the cassowaries' enclosure; and milking a king brown snake.

7.title: Wrangling Wild Wombats

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

7.plot: Faulkner supports the conversation of southern hairy-nosed wombat populations while traveling through South Australia. In addition, he encounters an owlet-nightjar and witnesses the hatching of rare dwarf king brown snake eggs.

8.title: Return to Kangaroo Island

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: Faulkner returns to Kangaroo Island for new adventures with the rare echidna, a colony of sea lions, and a mob of the hopping marsupials for which is the island's namesake.

9.title: Frogs of the Gold Coast

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

9.plot: Faulkner travels to southern Queensland to learn more about frog conservation efforts and to search for some of the region's endangered amphibians throughout the Gold Coast Hinterland.

10.title: Pups and Joeys

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: Faulkner spends time with two young kangaroo joey orphans and newborn dingo pups.

11.title: The Journey of the Loggerhead

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

11.plot: Faulkner travels north to Queensland to witness loggerhead sea turtles laying eggs and their hatchlings making their first journey into the ocean. In Western Australia, he supports removing a king brown snake from a resident's shed.

12.title: A Clean Bilby of Health

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

12.plot: Faulkner welcomes two bilby joeys and gives them a check-up. In addition, he travels to Watagans National Park to help capture deadly funnel-web spiders for the Reptile Park's venom program.

13.title: Western Australia Lizard Expedition

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

13.plot: Faulkner travels to the Dampier Peninsula in Western Australia where he finds a variety of lizards and snakes. Faulkner subsequently visits Hunter Valley Zoo to assist with antelope grooming while being closer to home.

14.title: Emus to Amuse

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

14.plot: Faulkner and his associates must catch mischievous emus within the Reptile Park and relocate them elsewhere. In addition, they must tag troublesome alligators for their identification.

15.title: Swimming with Sharks

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

15.plot: Faulkner goes on an underwater adventure involving sharks. In addition, he visits a bird sanctuary on Kangaroo Island to get up close to a Wedge Tailed Eagle.

16.title: A Globe of Frogs

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

16.plot: Faulkner explores the frogs inhabiting Watagans National Park; researches the red-backed toadlet; and discovers the unique features of Fraser Island.

17.title: Diamond Pythons and Pygmy Lizards

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

17.plot: Faulkner rescues a diamond python from a family's drainpipe; and travels to South Australia on a search for the pygmy blue tongue skink. He also seeks for a rare lizard long believed to be extinct.

18.title: The Richness of Roebuck Bay

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

18.plot: Faulkner travels to Western Australia and uncovers the mysteries of Roebuck Bay from curious creatures hidden in mud to numerous migrating birds as well as a newly discovered dolphin species.

19.title: The Wonders of Wilpena Pound

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

19.plot: Faulkner travels to Wilpena Pound in South Australia to check on conservation efforts for two particular endangered marsupials which are quolls and yellow-footed rock wallabies.

20.title: The Road to Windjana

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

20.plot: Faulkner goes on a search for tiger snakes on Kangaroo Island, travels to Western Australia to find freshwater crocodiles, and journeys to the legendary Windjana Gorge.

21.title: Myths from a Land Down Under

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

21.plot: Faulkner explores a variety of Aboriginal myths about Australian wildlife and assists with an enormous saltwater crocodile named Bluey in Western Australia.

22.title: Tim and the Tazzies

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

22.plot: Faulkner is on an investigating research about rescuing the Tasmanian devil population from extinction. In addition, he delves into a mysterious world of venomous snakes.

23.title: Be Wary of the Cassowary

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

23.plot: Faulkner's task is a cassowary matchmaker. In addition, he assists in catching an aggressive antelope and welcomes dwarf king snakelets to the Australian Reptile Park.

24.title: The Marsupials of Dryandra

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

24.plot: Faulkner travels to the Dryandra Woodlands in Western Australia to go on a search for endangered numbats and woylies.

25.title: Capturing Clever Koalas

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

25.plot: Faulkner travels to Kangaroo Island to learn about the conservation for the koala population. In addition, he assists in the removal of a king brown snake from a resident's shed while visiting Western Australia.

26.title: South Australian Stories

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

26.plot: Faulkner journeys to South Australia for adventures with the southern hairy nosed wombat and a colony of sea lions.

1.title: Speak of the Tasmanian Devil

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

1.plot: Faulkner visits the Tasmanian Devil Sanctuary to meet the new babies; a peregrine falcon cries for help; and a crocodile needs his cage cleaned up for visitors.

2.title: Rock Pools and Curlew Chicks

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

2.plot: Faulkner takes great care of a pair of adorable Bush Stone-curlew chicks, explores rock pools in Tasmania for bizarre creatures of the sea, and ventures into the Outback in search of the mighty perentie.

3.title: Home on the West Macdonnell Ranges

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

3.plot: Faulkner explores the West MacDonnell Ranges of Central Australia and encounters rock-wallabies, a wide assortment of frogs, and elusive dingoes.

4.title: Wombat and Koala Adventures

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

4.plot: Faulkner visits a pond west of Sydney is search of platypus, travels to the Northern Territory to catch a rogue crocodile, and comes back home to spend some quality time with a wombat and a koala couple.

5.title: Caring for Cormorants

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

5.plot: Faulkner comes to an injured cormorant's aid; meets a rare white crocodile; and finds a few marvelous frogs in a forest.

6.title: The Cutest Little Devils

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

6.plot: Audiences learn from Faulkner about Tasmanian devils which inhabit the Australian island, Tasmania.

7.title: Reptile Babies

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

7.plot: Faulkner travels north to find crocodile hatchlings and subsequently returns to the Reptile Park for some snakelets. In addition, he gets up close to a gigantic tortoise.

8.title: Bird is the Word

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

8.plot: Faulkner work with cassowaries at the Reptile Park. In addition, he comes to a peregrine falcon's aid. Other than birds, Faulkner and his associates trap a troubled crocodile when they travel to Darwin.

9.title: Gator Down Under

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

9.plot: Faulkner assists moving an alligator out of mud; cares for young Tasmanian devils; and meets some marmoset monkeys.

10.title: Elvis and Bowerbirds

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

10.plot: Faulkner explores the world of the western bowerbird species; participates in a cassowary conservation; and examines an injured foot of a gigantic saltwater crocodile named Elvis.

11.title: Dingoes, Dragons and Devils

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

11.plot: Faulkner gets to know about dingo pups; introduces a Komodo dragon to some new friends; and checks in on the Tasmanian devil rehabilitation program.

12.title: Chasing Rock Wallabies

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

12.plot: Faulkner and his associates at the Reptile Park try to catch yellow-footed rock wallabies to give them a check-up, seek for scrub pythons in the trees, and visit fur seals on Tasman Island.

13.title: Koala on the Loose

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

13.plot: Faulkner and his associates notice a koala being loose inside the Reptile Park. In addition, he seeks for wombats and kangaroos in Tasmania.

14.title: Babies and Chicks

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

14.plot: Faulkner supports hatching some alligator eggs, works with a rescued cassowary chick, and rehabilitates fruit bats.

15.title: Roos in the Trees

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

15.plot: Faulkner visits a tree kangaroo rehabilitation center in Queensland; checks on the health of the platypus population of Fish River; and feeds a giant crocodile named Elvis at the Reptile Park.

16.title: Snake School

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

16.plot: Faulkner visits Tasmania to meet a Tasmanian devil survivor named Neville and Wilbur the willful wombat. He subsequently returns to the Reptile Park to train young keepers in snake handling.

17.title: Reptiles on the Move

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

17.plot: Faulkner and his associates from the Australian Reptile Park relocate Brutus the alligator. In addition, Leonardo the snapping goes for his weigh-in.

18.title: Captain Kangaroo

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

18.plot: Faulkner visits northern Queensland to assist with the rehab of Kimberly, a colicky young tree kangaroo; and supports removing a dangerous death adder from a couple's yard.

19.title: Catch and Release

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

19.plot: It is snake season in Tasmania and release day for one lucky turtle. Faulkner and his crew later try to get a handle on Atomic Betty.

20.title: Daddy Day Care

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

20.plot: Faulkner brings his son Bill to the park to help out with its animals. Then, he supports removing some unwanted guests from a local home; and goes on snake patrol in Alice Springs.

21.title: Kangaroo Jack

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

21.plot: Faulkner explores the marvelous features of the kangaroo; highlights Tasmania for its three snake species; and gets some assistance from his son Bill at the Reptile Park.

22.title: Bower Power

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

22.plot: Faulkner finds golden bower birds and their elaborate bowers; looks for wild tree kangaroos; and takes his son Bill to the park to help out with the koalas and a chameleon.

23.title: Fine Feathered Friends

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

23.plot: Faulkner gives aid to an injured cormorant, feeds bush-stone curlew chicks and checks in on a cassowary chick with a surprising best friend.

24.title: Wacky Wombats and Wallabies

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

24.plot: Faulkner tries to catch rock-wallabies for a check-up and spends some time with wombats at the Reptile Park and in Australian wildernesses.

25.title: Koalas and Crocs

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

25.plot: Faulkner explores crocodile conservation in Queensland; seeks for a missing koala; and receives some encouragement at the Reptile Park from his young son Bill.

26.title: Tree Kangaroo Tales

episode of.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner (TV Series 2014– )

26.plot: Faulkner travels around Australia to learn more about the condition of the elusive tree kangaroo species.

imdb.title: Outback Adventures with Tim Faulkner
plot: An educational reality television series that showcases an introduction to a variety of Australian animals whether in the outback or at the Australian Reptile Park.::Anonymous
